From c68c6992b58bb2b794e1d1f8d4bd35c60c75f139 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Sat, 23 May 2026 13:33:17 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix: remediate audit vulnerabilities via yarn resolutions and
 dep bumps
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- bump direct devDeps: marked ^2→^4.0.10, rollup ^2.47→^2.80.0, lodash ^4.17→^4.18.0
- remove vue-server-renderer (unused devDep; carried lodash.template vuln)
- add comprehensive yarn resolutions for critical/high transitive vulns:
  pbkdf2, sha.js, form-data, handlebars, json-schema, @babel/traverse,
  braces, cross-spawn, semver, minimatch, serialize-javascript, flatted,
  picomatch, immutable, follow-redirects, tar-fs, ssri, qs, ws, micromatch,
  brace-expansion, yaml, tmp, diff, @tootallnate/once, lodash, axios, tar,
  http-cache-semantics, glob, svgo, defu, devalue, js-cookie, fast-uri,
  @babel/plugin-transform-modules-systemjs, bn.js
- remaining 14 HIGH advisories are all in docs-only devDeps (nuxt, codesandbox,
  @nuxtjs/pwa) with no available patch; excluded by improved-yarn-audit
  --ignore-dev-deps, which passes with 0 vulnerabilities
- tests: 164/164 suites pass
---
 package.json |   52 +-
 yarn.lock    | 1730 ++++++++++++++++----------------------------------
 2 files changed, 584 insertions(+), 1198 deletions(-)

